= Load Sequence VDBs =
#context: lop
#type: node

"""Loads a VDB file sequence into a USD stage as a Volume with one OpenVDB primitive per grid."""

== Overview ==

Load Sequence VDBs creates a USD layer containing a Volume primitive with one child OpenVDB primitive per grid name. Each OpenVDB primitive is connected to the Volume by a field relationship, and its `filePath`, `fieldName`, and `fieldIndex` properties are time-sampled to match the VDB file sequence frame range.

By default no extent (bounding box) data is written. Enable __ExtentsHint From File__ to compute and write time-sampled `extentsHint`, or add it downstream with __Manually Set ExtentsHint__.

@parameters

Parent Primitive:
    #id: parent_primpath
    Root path under which the Volume primitive will be created.

Primitive Name:
    #id: prim_name
    Name of the Volume primitive. The OpenVDB primitive will be created as a child of this prim.

VDB Files:
    #id: files
    File path pattern for the VDB sequence. Supports `$F` frame substitution.

Start/End:
    #id: frame_range
    Frame range of the VDB sequence.

Grids:
    #id: grids
    Space-separated list of VDB grid names to include in the OpenVDB primitive.

Grid Index:
    #id: grid_index
    Index of the grid within the VDB file. Usually `0`. Increase if multiple grids share the same name. Applied to every grid in the list.

ExtentsHint From File:
    #id: extentshint_from_file
    When enabled, loads each VDB file per frame to compute its bounding box and writes a time-sampled `extentsHint` on the Volume. Accurate but slow, since every file in the frame range is opened.
